      { "from": "event pipeline", "to": "dead-letter queue", "status": "broken", "issue": "DLQ exists but has no consumer. Failed events accumulate indefinitely with no processing, no alerting, and no visibility. This is a silent data loss path disguised as a resilience feature." }
    ],
    "contract_compliance": "HTTP ingestion and internal pipeline contracts appear sound. The contract between pipeline and data warehouse is violated by the lack of idempotency — the retry contract assumes safe retries, but the warehouse does not honor that assumption.",
    "data_flow_integrity": "Compromised. Two independent paths produce duplicate records: (1) circuit breaker recovery retries already-written events, (2) at-least-once delivery retries events whose ACK was lost. Without deduplication, downstream analytics consumers will report inflated numbers. Additionally, the DLQ represents a dead-end data path — events that land there are effectively lost."
  },

  "observability_review": {
    "logging": { "coverage": "adequate", "gaps": [] },
    "metrics": { "coverage": "adequate", "gaps": ["No metric tracking duplicate event writes", "No metric for DLQ depth or age of oldest message", "No metric distinguishing genuine new events from retried duplicates"] },
