      "DLQ behavior under sustained warehouse outage — no visibility into growth rate or storage limits",
      "Migration strategy for adding deduplication to an already high-volume table"
    ],
    "assumptions": [
      "The data warehouse does not have its own deduplication layer (e.g., UPSERT or merge-on-read)",
      "Downstream analytics consumers do not deduplicate on read",
      "The DLQ has no TTL or retention policy that would auto-purge old messages"
    ]
  }
}

